Third-party attribution
-----------------------

iLEAPP — iOS Logs, Events, And Plist Parser
  https://github.com/abrignoni/iLEAPP
  MIT License.

  Used with attribution per its license. The M0 schema spike cross-referenced
  iLEAPP's parsing logic — notably scripts/artifacts/sms.py — to validate the
  messages domain: Cocoa/nanosecond timestamp conversion, attributedBody /
  typedstream handling, join topology, and attachment-path handling. Where later
  milestones translate any iLEAPP parsing logic into Go, that code is additionally
  attributed inline at the call site.

  M1 (contacts) additionally cross-referenced scripts/artifacts/addressBook.py
  for the ABMultiValue property constants (3 phone / 4 email / 5 address /
  13 instant message / 22 URL / 23 related names / 46 profiles) and the
  "_$!<Label>!$_" built-in label wrapper (attributed inline in
  contacts/schema.go and contacts/label.go). iLEAPP is also the differential
  oracle for contacts (testing ladder rung 3), run as an installed tool in its
  own container.

  M2 (calls) additionally cross-referenced scripts/artifacts/callHistory.py for
  the ZCALLRECORD interpretations: ZCALLTYPE (0 third-party app / 1 phone /
  8 FaceTime video / 16 FaceTime audio), ZORIGINATED (0 incoming / 1 outgoing)
  and ZANSWERED (0/1) — attributed inline in calls/types.go and
  deploy/diff_calls.py. iLEAPP is also the differential oracle for calls.

imessage-exporter (GPL) is used ONLY as a black-box differential oracle — executed
and compared against, never read or ported. No GPL-licensed code is incorporated
into this repository.
